{{Notability|Academics|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Reza Sadeghi | image =R.Sadeghi.JPG | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = April 20, 1977 | birth_place = [[Mashad]], [[Iran]] | residence = | nationality = [[Iran]]ian | field = [[Mathematician]] | work_institutions = | alma_mater = [[Sharif University of Technology]] | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = | known_for = | prizes = | footnotes = }} '''Reza Sadeghi ''' ({{lang-fa|رضا صادقی}};(April 20, 1977 – March 17, 1998) was an [[Iran]]ian [[mathematician]]. He is an alumnus of National Organization for Development of Exceptional Talents (NODET) Mashad, Iran (Hasheminejad highschool).<ref>http://www.hn1.sampadrazavi.ir/view.aspx?kh=2&cod=12{{dead link|date=April 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
==Prizes== Reza Sadeghi won the silver medal in the [[International Mathematical Olympiad]] in Hong Kong in 1994. He won the gold medal in the [[International Mathematical Olympiad]] in Canada in 1995.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imo-official.org/search.aspx|title=International Mathematical Olympiad|website=www.imo-official.org}}</ref>
